    "statementHTML": "<div class=\"statement-body\">\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-goal\">\n   <h2><span class=\"icon icon-goal\">&nbsp;</span><span>Goal </span></h2>\n   <span class=\"question-statement\">This is <strong>Chapter 1</strong> of the <strong>Digital Logic Basics</strong> series.<br>In this chapter, you will evaluate the output of a single logic gate given its binary input value(s).<br>A logic gate takes one or two binary inputs (<const>0</const> or <const>1</const>) and produces a binary output according to a well‑defined rule.<br>The supported gates in this puzzle are:<br><const>BUFFER</const>, <const>NOT</const>, <const>AND</const>, <const>OR</const>, <const>NAND</const>, <const>NOR</const>, <const>XOR</const>, <const>XNOR</const></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-protocol\">\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-input\"><strong>Line 1:</strong> A string <var>G</var> &mdash; the gate name.<br><strong>Line 2:</strong> Either<br><br>One integer <var>A</var> (for BUFFER, NOT), or<br>Two integers <var>A</var> and <var>B</var> (for all binary gates).</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-output\"><strong>Line 1:</strong> A single integer (0 or 1) &mdash; the output of gate <var>G</var>.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Constraints</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-constraints\"><var>G</var> &isin; {BUFFER, NOT, AND, OR, NAND, NOR, XOR, XNOR}<br><var>A</var>, <var>B</var> &isin; {0, 1}</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Example</div>\n      <div class=\"statement-inout\">\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-in\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-in\">BUFFER\n0</pre>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-out\">\n